23/01/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia will hold municipal and regional elections on 15 May, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader announced Saturday (22 January). 
Local observers see the vote as a test for his government and the ruling HDZ party in the wake of its defeat in the recent presidential election.
In other news, the city of Dubrovnik has made former EU External Relations Commissioner Chris Patten an honorary citizen. 
The British diplomat was honoured for his efforts to bring Croatia closer to EU membership. 
(AFP - 22/01/05)
